FBIS4-1248 "drafr079_c_94035" FBIS-AFR-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA No Role in Election Security No Role in Election Security MB2204165794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1600 GMT 22 Apr 94 MB2204165794 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The National Peacekeeping Force will not play any part in election security. This role will be performed exclusively by the police and defense force. Major General Gert Opperman of the SADF [South African Defense Force] said that members of the SADF would be deployed near voting stations, while the SAP [South African Police] would be responsible for the immediate security of the voting stations.
